Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:01.000 --> 00:00:05.000
 The Jinfeng 2000 Bridge. 

00:00:06.000 --> 00:00:10.000
 Moso-dake (Someso bamboo) which becomes material of bamboo lanterns. 

00:00:11.000 --> 00:00:14.000
 Cut the bamboo. 

00:00:14.000 --> 00:00:17.000
 Take-off angle is 20 degrees. 

00:00:17.000 --> 00:00:20.000
 45 degrees for exhibition and lighting. 

00:00:28.000 --> 00:00:32.000
 When making a long lantern, remove the clause with a chisel. 

00:00:35.000 --> 00:00:38.000
 Trace paper pattern. 

00:00:39.000 --> 00:00:43.000
 Put a pattern on bamboo and take pictures. 

00:00:54.000 --> 00:00:58.000
 Drill a hole at the point of the picture. 

00:01:18.000 --> 00:01:22.000
 Connect the holes with an air saw (saw). 

00:01:40.000 --> 00:01:44.000
 I scoop the surface of bamboo with a burner and blow off the water. 

00:01:44.000 --> 00:01:48.000
 If it does not dry and it wipes quickly, it will be finished in good color. 

00:01:52.000 --> 00:01:55.000
 Completed bamboo lanterns. 

00:01:56.000 --> 00:02:00.000
 Light a cup of candle. 

00:02:00.000 --> 00:02:04.000
 The flame sways due to the wind from the side hole. 

